{"author":{"uri":{"label":"https://itunes.apple.com/us/reviews/id1568476473"}, "name":{"label":"Marveloux999"}, "label":""}, "updated":{"label":"2026-05-24T00:16:38-07:00"}, "im:rating":{"label":"1"}, "im:version":{"label":"26.19.77"}, "id":{"label":"14099642531"}, "title":{"label":"No way to restore chats!"}, "content":{"label":"Critical UX and security inconsistency related to Passkeys and encrypted iCloud backups in WhatsApp for iOS.\n\nScenario:\n* I enabled Passkey authentication in WhatsApp.\n* I accidentally deleted the app and reinstalled it.\n* During the restore process, WhatsApp requested the application password for the encrypted iCloud backup.\n* There is NO option to authenticate using the Passkey.\n\nProblem:\nThe user experience strongly suggests that the Passkey replaces traditional credentials, yet encrypted backup restoration still depends on a separate hidden password that may not exist in iCloud Keychain or be visible or manageable by the user.\n\nThis creates a severe lockout scenario where:\n\n* backups exist,\n* the user identity is successfully verified,\n* the Passkey works correctly,\n* but historical encrypted data becomes permanently inaccessible.\n\nI can’t believe theres a huge gap on trust and reliability.", "attributes":{"type":"text"}}, "link":{"attributes":{"rel":"related", "href":"https://itunes.apple.com/us/review?id=310633997&type=Purple%20Software"}}, "im:voteSum":{"label":"0"}, "im:contentType":{"attributes":{"term":"Application", "label":"Application"}}, "im:voteCount":{"label":"0"}},
